{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "property-image-management",
    "name": "Property Image Management",
    "description": "Complete API collection for property image management.\n\n## Features\n- File uploads via multipart/form-data\n- URL-based image imports\n- External image references\n- Batch uploads (up to 20 images)\n- Automatic image optimization\n- Thumbnail generation\n- Image metadata management\n\n## Requirements\n- Cloudinary account and credentials configured\n- Valid authentication token\n- Existing property ID\n\n## Supported Formats\n- JPEG\n- PNG\n- WebP\n- GIF\n\n## Size Limits\n- Max file size: 10MB\n- Max batch size: 20 images\n- Max images per property: 50",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "{{base_url}}",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "📋 Read Operations",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get All Property Images",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response has success true', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true);",
                  "pm.test('Response has images array', () => {",
                  "    const data = pm.response.json().data;",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Save first image ID if exists",
                  "const data = pm.response.json().data;",
                  "if (data && data.length > 0) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('image_id', data[0].id);",
                  "    if (data[0].public_id) {",
                  "        pm.environment.set('image_public_id', data[0].public_id);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{platform_admin_access_token}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/properties/{{property_id}}/images",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "properties", "{{property_id}}", "images"]
            },
            "description": "Retrieve all images for a specific property, sorted by sort_order."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success Response",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "GET",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/properties/{{property_id}}/images"
                }
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"message\": \"Images retrieved successfully\",\n  \"data\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"507f1f77bcf86cd799439012\",\n      \"property_id\": \"507f1f77bcf86cd799439011\",\n      \"url\": \"https://res.cloudinary.com/.../image1.webp\",\n      \"secure_url\": \"https://res.cloudinary.com/.../image1.webp\",\n      \"thumbnail_url\": \"https://res.cloudinary.com/.../c_fill,h_300,w_400/image1.webp\",\n      \"public_id\": \"immobilier/properties/.../image1\",\n      \"width\": 1920,\n      \"height\": 1080,\n      \"format\": \"webp\",\n      \"bytes\": 245789,\n      \"alt_text\": \"Living room\",\n      \"caption\": \"Spacious living area\",\n      \"sort_order\": 0,\n      \"is_primary\": true,\n      \"source\": \"cloudinary\",\n      \"created_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00.000Z\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Image Count",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response has count', () => {",
                  "    const data = pm.response.json().data;",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('count');",
                  "    pm.expect(data.count).to.be.a('number');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{platform_admin_access_token}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/properties/{{property_id}}/images/count",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "properties", "{{property_id}}", "images", "count"]
            },
            "description": "Get the total count of images for a property."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success Response",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"message\": \"Image count retrieved successfully\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"count\": 5\n  }\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Signed Upload URL",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response has upload URL data', () => {",
                  "    const data = pm.response.json().data;",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('uploadUrl');",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('signature');",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('timestamp');",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('apiKey');",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('cloudName');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const data = pm.response.json().data;",
                  "    pm.environment.set('cloudinary_upload_url', data.uploadUrl);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('cloudinary_signature', data.signature);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('cloudinary_timestamp', data.timestamp);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{platform_admin_access_token}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/properties/{{property_id}}/images/upload-url",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "properties", "{{property_id}}", "images", "upload-url"]
            },
            "description": "Get a signed URL for direct client-side uploads to Cloudinary. This enables browser-based uploads without going through the server."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success Response",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"message\": \"Upload URL generated successfully\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"uploadUrl\": \"https://api.cloudinary.com/v1_1/your-cloud/image/upload\",\n    \"signature\": \"abc123signature\",\n    \"timestamp\": 1704067200,\n    \"apiKey\": \"123456789012345\",\n    \"cloudName\": \"your-cloud\"\n  }\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "description": "Read-only operations for retrieving image data."
    },
    {
      "name": "📤 Upload Operations",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Upload Single Image (File)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Response has success true', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true);",
                  "pm.test('Image has required fields', () => {",
                  "    const data = pm.response.json().data;",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('id');",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('url');",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('secure_url');",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('public_id');",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('width');",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('height');",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('format');",
                  "    pm.expect(data.source).to.equal('cloudinary');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const data = pm.response.json().data;",
                  "    pm.environment.set('image_id', data.id);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('image_public_id', data.public_id);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{platform_admin_access_token}}"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "image",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": "",
                  "description": "Required. Image file (JPEG, PNG, WebP, GIF). Max 10MB."
                },
                {
                  "key": "alt_text",
                  "value": "Property living room",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Optional. Alternative text for accessibility."
                },
                {
                  "key": "caption",
                  "value": "Spacious living area with natural lighting",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Optional. Image caption/description."
                },
                {
                  "key": "is_primary",
                  "value": "true",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Optional. Set as primary property image. Default: false"
                },
                {
                  "key": "sort_order",
                  "value": "0",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Optional. Display order (0 = first)."
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/properties/{{property_id}}/images/upload",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "properties", "{{property_id}}", "images", "upload"]
            },
            "description": "Upload a single image file via multipart/form-data.\n\n## Processing\n1. Image is received and stored in memory\n2. Preprocessed with Sharp (resize, optimize)\n3. Uploaded to Cloudinary\n4. Thumbnail generated automatically\n5. Metadata saved to database\n\n## Limits\n- Max file size: 10MB\n- Supported formats: JPEG, PNG, WebP, GIF"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success Response",
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"message\": \"Image uploaded successfully\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"id\": \"507f1f77bcf86cd799439012\",\n    \"property_id\": \"507f1f77bcf86cd799439011\",\n    \"url\": \"http://res.cloudinary.com/.../image.webp\",\n    \"secure_url\": \"https://res.cloudinary.com/.../image.webp\",\n    \"thumbnail_url\": \"http://res.cloudinary.com/.../c_fill,h_300,w_400/image.webp\",\n    \"thumbnail_secure_url\": \"https://res.cloudinary.com/.../c_fill,h_300,w_400/image.webp\",\n    \"public_id\": \"immobilier/properties/507f1f77bcf86cd799439011/1703123456789-abc123\",\n    \"width\": 1920,\n    \"height\": 1080,\n    \"format\": \"webp\",\n    \"bytes\": 245789,\n    \"alt_text\": \"Property living room\",\n    \"caption\": \"Spacious living area with natural lighting\",\n    \"sort_order\": 0,\n    \"is_primary\": true,\n    \"source\": \"cloudinary\",\n    \"original_filename\": \"living-room.jpg\",\n    \"created_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00.000Z\"\n  }\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Upload Multiple Images (Batch)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Response has successful and failed arrays', () => {",
                  "    const data = pm.response.json().data;",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('successful');",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('failed');",
                  "    pm.expect(data.successful).to.be.an('array');",
                  "    pm.expect(data.failed).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Save first successful image ID",
                  "const data = pm.response.json().data;",
                  "if (data.successful && data.successful.length > 0) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('image_id', data.successful[0].id);",
                  "    if (data.successful[0].public_id) {",
                  "        pm.environment.set('image_public_id', data.successful[0].public_id);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{platform_admin_access_token}}"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "images",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": "",
                  "description": "Required. Multiple image files. Select multiple files in file dialog."
                },
                {
                  "key": "alt_text",
                  "value": "Property photos",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Optional. Alt text applied to all images."
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/properties/{{property_id}}/images/upload-multiple",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "properties", "{{property_id}}", "images", "upload-multiple"]
            },
            "description": "Upload multiple images in a single request.\n\n## Processing\nEach image is processed sequentially and results are returned in a batch response.\n\n## Limits\n- Max 20 images per request\n- Max 10MB per file\n- Total request size depends on server config"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success Response",
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"message\": \"Images uploaded successfully\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"successful\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"507f1f77bcf86cd799439012\",\n        \"property_id\": \"507f1f77bcf86cd799439011\",\n        \"url\": \"https://res.cloudinary.com/.../living-room.webp\",\n        \"public_id\": \"immobilier/properties/.../living-room\",\n        \"width\": 1920,\n        \"height\": 1080,\n        \"format\": \"webp\",\n        \"bytes\": 245789,\n        \"source\": \"cloudinary\",\n        \"original_filename\": \"living-room.jpg\",\n        \"created_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00.000Z\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"507f1f77bcf86cd799439013\",\n        \"property_id\": \"507f1f77bcf86cd799439011\",\n        \"url\": \"https://res.cloudinary.com/.../bedroom.webp\",\n        \"public_id\": \"immobilier/properties/.../bedroom\",\n        \"width\": 1920,\n        \"height\": 1080,\n        \"format\": \"webp\",\n        \"bytes\": 198456,\n        \"source\": \"cloudinary\",\n        \"original_filename\": \"bedroom.jpg\",\n        \"created_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:01.000Z\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"failed\": [\n      {\n        \"filename\": \"kitchen.jpg\",\n        \"error\": \"File size exceeds maximum allowed limit\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}"
            }
          ]
